text:
Social Conditions in Manhattan: In this 2 room apartment at No. 263 Stanton Street, live a father, a mother, two children and a boarder-- 5 in all. The foreground is the kitchen, living and dining room in the day time which at night becomes a "Pullman car;" two folding cots being stretched out. Undoubtedly published by the New York Evening World of this date.

November 27, 1923.

Gift of New York World.
title: Social conditions - [Interior of a two-room apartment.]
